    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public final void execute(TemplateModel[] args,
                          CallPlace callPlace,
                          Writer out,
                          Environment env)
                   throws TemplateException,
                          IOException
        Execute this directive.

        This method establishes Spring's RequestContext and invokes executeInternal(TemplateModel[], CallPlace, Writer, Environment, ObjectWrapperAndUnwrapper, RequestContext) which must be implemented by derived directive classes.

        Specified by:
        execute in interface TemplateDirectiveModel
        Parameters:
        args - The array of argument values. Not null. If a parameter was omitted on the caller side, the corresponding array element will be null. The length of the array and the indexes correspond to the ArgumentArrayLayout returned by TemplateDirectiveModel.getDirectiveArgumentArrayLayout(). ArgumentArrayLayout os not nullm and the caller doesn't keep argument layout rules (such as the array is shorter than ArgumentArrayLayout.getTotalLength(), or the type of the values at ArgumentArrayLayout.getPositionalVarargsArgumentIndex() or at ArgumentArrayLayout.getNamedVarargsArgumentIndex() is improper), this method may throws IndexOutOfBoundsException or ClassCastException. Thus, user Java code that wishes to call TemplateCallableModel-s is responsible to ensure that the argument array follows the layout described be ArgumentArrayLayout, as the execute method isn't meant to do validations on that level.
        callPlace - The place (in a template, normally) where this directive was called from. Not null; in case the call is not from a template, you can use NonTemplateCallPlace.INSTANCE (or another NonTemplateCallPlace instance). Note that CallPlace.executeNestedContent(TemplateModel[], Writer, Environment) can be used to execute the nested content (even if there's no nested content; then simply nothing happens), and to pass nested content parameters to it.
        out - Print the output here (if there's any)
        env - The current processing environment. Not null in general, though certain implementations may specifically allow that, typically, implementations that are just adapters towards FreeMarker-unaware callables (for example, JavaMethodModel is like that).
        Throws:
        TemplateException - If any problem occurs that's not an IOException during writing the template output.
        IOException - When writing the template output fails.
